  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study was to investigate changes in abdominal tissue perfusion during
      adenosine vasodilation. Our hypotheses were that CT perfusion measurements are altered by
      changes in the circulatory system mediated by adenosine, and a more differentiated assessment
      of the circulatory capacity of abdominal tumours could be achieved by sequential rest and
      adenosine vasodilation CT perfusion measurements.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
